### Key changes summarised

| Area | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Config format | HCL `.maglev` file | YAML `config/gcp.yaml` |
| Config schema | `maglev`, `node`, `node_pool`, `gcp_config` blocks | `group`, `generics`, `specs`, `rules`, `credentials` keys |
| Provider abstraction | Free functions in `gcp.rs` | `Provider` trait in `mod.rs`; `GcpProvider` struct implements it |
| Auth context | Passed as `&str` arguments | Owned by `GcpProvider` (constructed once via `::new`) |
| JWT / token logic | `main.rs` | `gcp.rs` (private to the provider) |
| HCL deps | `hcl` crate | Removed — replaced by `serde_yaml` |
| `utils.rs` | Included `load_gcp_private_key` | Removed (moved into `GcpProvider::new`) |

The closure cannot carry explicit lifetime annotations. The simplest fix is to return owned `String` names instead of borrowing `&str` from the slice.

Change the closure and its call-sites in `play_config`:

```rust
